<div id="review_3804068087" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3804068087" />
    <a title="Pam Jenoff" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4980927-pam-jenoff"><img alt="Pam Jenoff" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1620813645p2/4980927.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3804068087?book_show_action=true">Jan 29, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pam Jenoff" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pam Jenoff" href="/user/show/4980927-pam-jenoff">Pam Jenoff</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3804068087" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1072808755232173252">Alyson is a master historical fiction writer and The Lost Wife is her most iconic work. At a wedding in present day New York, an elderly man spots a familiar woman across the room and realizes that it is his wife, whom he has long thought lost during the Second World War. The book then spirals back to their life before and during the war in Prague. If you love WW2 fiction, this is certainly one of the best!</span>

          </span>
        </div>


