        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer529394460" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8594464819342282816">The cause of my latest book hangover:<br/><br/>An elderly man is sitting at his grandson&apos;s rehearsal dinner when suddenly a woman catches his eye from across the room. He goes to her, transfixed, and looks at her like he&apos;s seen a ghost. This woman, the grandmother of the bride, does not recognize him but he remembers her. &quot;Lenka&quot;, he says, &quot;it&apos;s me Josef. Your husband.&quot; <br/><br/>And that was all it took to suck me in...<br/><br/>Set against the backdrop of WWII Europe, The Lost Wife tells the story of Lenka and Josef young </span>
  <span id="freeText8594464819342282816" style="display:none">The cause of my latest book hangover:<br /><br />An elderly man is sitting at his grandson's rehearsal dinner when suddenly a woman catches his eye from across the room. He goes to her, transfixed, and looks at her like he's seen a ghost. This woman, the grandmother of the bride, does not recognize him but he remembers her. "Lenka", he says, "it's me Josef. Your husband." <br /><br />And that was all it took to suck me in...<br /><br />Set against the backdrop of WWII Europe, The Lost Wife tells the story of Lenka and Josef young lovers who's lives and marriage are torn apart by the Nazi occupation. The book alternates narrators between Lenka and Josef and we get to learn about both sides of their war experience. Josef's escape to America, Lenka's time in the camps, a story of love, loss, and life. <br /><br />You rarely find me gushing about a book here in more than a few words "I loved it" or something like that, but I felt this book deserved more. The Lost Wife was a wonderful book that was made even better by it's Audible narrators. I give the book 4 1/2 stars but the audible gets 5 stars. </span>
  <a data-text-id="8594464819342282816" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
