<div id="review_364041628" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/364041628" />
    <a title="Hermien" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5930747-hermien"><img alt="Hermien" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1312263837p2/5930747.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/364041628?book_show_action=true">Jul 08, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hermien" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hermien" href="/user/show/5930747-hermien">Hermien</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5930747-hermien?shelf=ebooks">ebooks</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5930747-hermien?shelf=wwi-ii">wwi-ii</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5930747-hermien?shelf=jewish">jewish</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5930747-hermien?shelf=eastern-europe">eastern-europe</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer364041628" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9272249609054938034">I have read many books dealing with the Holocaust, but found this one really disappointing. Josef and Lenka tell their story in the first person but it feels like it was written by a high school student using language and expressing feelings that people of Jozef and Lenka&apos;s age and era would never have used. There is no depth in the characters and even Lenka&apos;s description of life in Theresienstadt is rather bland. The interesting historical part of how the artists managed to let the outside worl</span>
  <span id="freeText9272249609054938034" style="display:none">I have read many books dealing with the Holocaust, but found this one really disappointing. Josef and Lenka tell their story in the first person but it feels like it was written by a high school student using language and expressing feelings that people of Jozef and Lenka's age and era would never have used. There is no depth in the characters and even Lenka's description of life in Theresienstadt is rather bland. The interesting historical part of how the artists managed to let the outside world know what was really going on is mentioned but remains a mystery as Lenka does not get involved in it. My impression was that the publishers and/or the writer thought "Let's do a book about a tragic love story set against the Holocaust, that'll sell!". </span>
  <a data-text-id="9272249609054938034" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


